---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. virutal function
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The pointer or reference to the base class calls the base version of the function 
rather than the derived version.

A virtual function is a special type of function that resolves to the most-derived 
version of the function with the same signature.

Note that virtual functions and virtual base classes are two entirely different 
concepts, even though they share the same keyword. 
